public class TextEncryptor {
    public String encrypt(String text, int shift) {
        char[] chars = text.toCharArray();
        for (int i = 0; i < chars.length; i++) {
            char c = chars[i];
            if (Character.isLetter(c)) {
                char base = Character.isUpperCase(c) ? 'A' : 'a';
                chars[i] = (char) (base + (c - base + shift) % 26);
            }
        }
        return new String(chars);
    }

    public String decrypt(String encryptedText, int shift) {
        return encrypt(encryptedText, 26 - shift); // Decryption is essentially encryption with the inverse shift
    }
}
```

The `encrypt` method iterates through each character in the input text, applies the shift to alphabetic characters, and constructs the encrypted text. The `decrypt` method leverages the `encrypt` method with an inverse shift to achieve the decryption process.

