Insertion sort is a simple sorting algorithm that works similarly to the way you sort playing cards in your hands. The array is virtually split into a sorted and an unsorted region. Values from the unsorted region are picked and placed at the correct position in the sorted region.

Here is a clean implementation of insertion sort in C++

```c++
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

void insertionSort(int arr[], int n) {
   int key, j;
   for(int i = 1; i<n; i++) {
      key = arr[i]; //take value
      j = i;
      while(j > 0 && arr[j-1]>key) {
         arr[j] = arr[j-1]; //shift number to one position ahead
         j--;
      }
      arr[j] = key; //insert in correct place
   }
}

void printArray(int arr[], int n) {
   for(int i = 0; i<n; i++)
      cout<< arr[i] <<" ";
