    cout << make_palindrome("") << endl;  // returns ""
    cout << make_palindrome("cat") << endl;  // returns "tacat"
    cout << make_palindrome("cato") << endl; // returns "otacato"
    return 0;
}
```

We have solved the above problem in O(n^2) time complexity. The inner while loop in the palindrome checking function runs O(n) times for each call, and it could be called O(n) times in the worst case in the main function. Hence, overall time complexity can be O(n^2), where n is the length of the string.

